approve(address,uint256).details: Approves another address to transfer the given token ID The zero address indicates there is no approved address. There can only be one approved address per token at a given time. Can only be called by the token owner or an approved operator.

params._to: address to be approved for the given token ID
params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be approved

artistsEditions(address).details: Lookup all editions for the given artist accountReturns empty list if not valid

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address

params._owner: address to query the balance of

balanceOf(address).return: uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address

batchTransfer(address,uint256[]).details: An extension to the default ERC721 behaviour, derived from ERC-875.Allowing for batch transfers from the sender, will fail if from does not own all the tokens

batchTransferFrom(address,address,uint25.details: An extension to the default ERC721 behaviour, derived from ERC-875.Allowing for batch transfers from the provided address, will fail if from does not own all the tokens

burn(uint256).details: Private (KO only) method for burning tokens which have been created incorrectly

createActiveEdition(uint256,bytes32,uint.details: Creates an active edition from the given configurationOnly callable from KO staff/addresses

createActivePreMintedEdition(uint256,byt.details: Creates an active edition from the given configurationThe concept of pre0minted editions means we can 'undermint' token IDS, good for holding back editions from public saleOnly callable from KO staff/addresses

createInactiveEdition(uint256,bytes32,ui.details: Creates an inactive edition from the given configurationOnly callable from KO staff/addresses

createInactivePreMintedEdition(uint256,b.details: Creates an inactive edition from the given configurationThe concept of pre0minted editions means we can 'undermint' token IDS, good for holding back editions from public saleOnly callable from KO staff/addresses

detailsOfEdition(uint256).details: Main entry point for looking up edition config/metadataReverts if invalid edition number provided

editionExists(uint256).details: Checks to see if the edition exists, assumes edition of zero is invalid

editionOfTokenId(uint256).details: Lookup the edition of the provided token IDReturns 0 if not valid

editionOptionalCommission(uint256).details: Lookup any optional commission split set for the editionBoth values will be zero if not present

editionsOfType(uint256).details: Lookup all editions added for the given edition typeReturns array of edition numbers, any zero edition ids can be ignore/stripped

exists(uint256).details: Returns whether the specified token exists

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query the existence of

getApproved(uint256).details: Gets the approved address for a token ID, or zero if no address set

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query the approval of

getApproved(uint256).return: address currently approved for the given token ID

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Tells whether an operator is approved by a given owner

params._operator: operator address which you want to query the approval of
params._owner: owner address which you want to query the approval of

isApprovedForAll(address,address).return: bool whether the given operator is approved by the given owner

mint(address,uint256).details: Private (KO only) method for minting editionsPayment not needed for this method

ownerOf(uint256).details: Gets the owner of the specified token ID

params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to query the owner of

ownerOf(uint256).return: owner address currently marked as the owner of the given token ID

pause().details: called by the owner to pause, triggers stopped state

purchase(uint256).details: Public entry point for purchasing an editionReverts if edition is invalidReverts if payment not provided in fullReverts if edition is sold outReverts if edition is not active or available

purchaseTo(address,uint256).details: Public entry point for purchasing an edition on behalf of someone elseReverts if edition is invalidReverts if payment not provided in fullReverts if edition is sold outReverts if edition is not active or available

reclaimEther().details: Transfer all Ether held by the contract to the owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a given token ID to another address If the target address is a contract, it must implement `onERC721Received`, which is called upon a safe transfer, and return the magic value `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,address,uint256,bytes)"))`; otherwise, the transfer is reverted.   * Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator

params._to: address to receive the ownership of the given token ID
params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be transferred

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Safely transfers the ownership of a given token ID to another address If the target address is a contract, it must implement `onERC721Received`, which is called upon a safe transfer, and return the magic value `bytes4(keccak256("onERC721Received(address,address,uint256,bytes)"))`; otherwise, the transfer is reverted. Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator

params._data: bytes data to send along with a safe transfer check
params._to: address to receive the ownership of the given token ID
params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be transferred

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Sets or unsets the approval of a given operator An operator is allowed to transfer all tokens of the sender on their behalf

params._approved: representing the status of the approval to be set
params._to: operator address to set the approval

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: implement supportsInterface(bytes4) using a lookup table

tokenByIndex(uint256).details: Gets the token ID at a given index of all the tokens in this contract Reverts if the index is greater or equal to the total number of tokens

params._index: uint256 representing the index to be accessed of the tokens list

tokenByIndex(uint256).return: uint256 token ID at the given index of the tokens list

tokenData(uint256).details: Lookup a tokens common identifying characteristicsReverts if invalid token ID provided

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).details: Gets the token ID at a given index of the tokens list of the requested owner

params._index: uint256 representing the index to be accessed of the requested tokens list
params._owner: address owning the tokens list to be accessed

tokenOfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).return: uint256 token ID at the given index of the tokens list owned by the requested address

tokensOf(address).details: Lookup all owned tokens for the provided addressReturns array of token IDs

tokensOfEdition(uint256).details: Lookup all tokens minted for the given edition numberReturns array of token IDs, any zero edition ids can be ignore/stripped

totalSupply().details: Gets the total amount of tokens stored by the contract
totalSupply().return: uint256 representing the total amount of tokens

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers the ownership of a given token ID to another address Usage of this method is discouraged, use `safeTransferFrom` whenever possible Requires the msg sender to be the owner, approved, or operator

params._to: address to receive the ownership of the given token ID
params._tokenId: uint256 ID of the token to be transferred

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params._newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

underMint(address,uint256).details: Private (KO only) method for under minting editionsUnder minting allows for token IDs to be back filled if total supply is not set to zero by defaultPayment not needed for this method

unpause().details: called by the owner to unpause, returns to normal state

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
